{\fs18\expnd0\expndtw0 Researchers have not agreed on a motor control explanation for the speed-accuracy trade-off. Below is a sampling of some of the prominent hypotheses that continue to have proponents. It is important to understand that these hypotheses relate to explanations for the speed-accuracy trade-off associated with rapid manual-aiming tasks, which were the types of tasks involved in the initial demonstrations of the trade-off. (See Elliott et al., \line }
{\fs18\expnd0\expndtw-2 2001, for a more detailed discussion of these, and other, hypotheses and of the research evidence related to them.)\par }
